## Additional Terms for Academic Use

### Citation Requirement

If you use this dataset or framework in academic research, please cite:

```bibtex
@article{okechukwu2024multimedia,
  title={Knowledge Extraction from Multimedia Data in Requirements Engineering: An Empirical Study},
  author={Okechukwu, Cornelius Chimuanya},
  journal={Requirements Engineering},
  year={2024},
  publisher={Springer},
  institution={Tomas Bata University in Zlin},
  doi={10.5281/zenodo.XXXXXX}
}
```

### Ethical Use Guidelines

Users of this dataset agree to:

1. **Respect Privacy**: The dataset is anonymized, maintain this anonymization
2. **Academic Integrity**: Properly cite and acknowledge the source
3. **Responsible Use**: Use the data for legitimate research and educational purposes
4. **Share Improvements**: Consider contributing improvements back to the community
5. **Report Issues**: Notify maintainers of any data quality issues discovered

### Data Usage Terms

- **Research Use**: Freely permitted for academic and commercial research
- **Educational Use**: Encouraged for teaching requirements engineering concepts  
- **Redistribution**: Permitted with proper attribution
- **Modification**: Allowed, but please document changes clearly
- **Commercial Use**: Permitted under the MIT license terms

### Disclaimer

This dataset is generated based on empirical research findings and is intended
for research and educational purposes. While efforts have been made to ensure
statistical accuracy and realism, users should validate the appropriateness
of this dataset for their specific research questions and contexts.

The synthetic nature of this dataset means it may not capture all nuances
present in real-world requirements engineering scenarios. Users should consider
supplementing with real-world data when appropriate for their research.

